        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Veterans' Access to Care Concerning Inoculations Needed in Emergency Situations Act or the VACCINES Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to furnish specified care during a public health emergency declared by a federal authority. Specifically, during such emergency, the VA must furnish to veterans (1) diagnostic products to detect the disease relating to the emergency, and (2) vaccinations for such disease.</p> <p>The VA may not require any copayment or other cost sharing for any diagnostic product or vaccine furnished under this bill.</p> <p>Additionally, the VA must conduct outreach to ensure that veterans are aware of the diagnostic products and vaccines available during the public health emergency.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
